Text.SourceString: Well, hello to yo–//ACHOOOOOO!//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… Spring. Not the best time to move here.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, hello to yo–//ACHOOOOOO!//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… Spring. Not the best time to move here.

Text.SourceString: By the way, I’m <NPCName>Char</>–//<portrait=surprised>ACHOOO!
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, I’m <NPCName>Char</>–//<portrait=surprised>ACHOOO!

Text.SourceString: Well, hello to you too! You must be new here.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, hello to you too! You must be new here.

Text.SourceString: I hope you like Coral Island. See you around!
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you like Coral Island. See you around!

Text.SourceString: The recycling center been here since…umm…
Text.LocalizedString: The recycling center been here since…umm…

Text.SourceString: I can’t remember for the life of me.//Tell you what, I’ll write you if it comes back to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t remember for the life of me.//Tell you what, I’ll write you if it comes back to me.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to be rude, but I wonder what you put in those pockets of yours.//<portrait=happy>They always seem so full.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to be rude, but I wonder what you put in those pockets of yours.//<portrait=happy>They always seem so full.

Text.SourceString: That reminds me. I forgot to take the recycling out yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: That reminds me. I forgot to take the recycling out yesterday.

Text.SourceString: I’m all for farming. I think it’s an excellent activity for both body and mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m all for farming. I think it’s an excellent activity for both body and mind.

Text.SourceString: You know what?//<portrait=normal>I wish more people would get out of their houses and do some farming. Or gardening. Get up and sweat it out!
Text.LocalizedString: You know what?//<portrait=normal>I wish more people would get out of their houses and do some farming. Or gardening. Get up and sweat it out!

Text.SourceString: Don’t you feel great after a good farming session, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you feel great after a good farming session, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: That’s what sunshine and physical activity does for you, my friend.//It gets the endorphins going – your feel-good chemicals.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what sunshine and physical activity does for you, my friend.//It gets the endorphins going – your feel-good chemicals.

Text.SourceString: Dehydration is a real thing. Your body’s mostly water, and it can’t work right without it. So, remember to stay hydrated, and drink plenty!
Text.LocalizedString: Dehydration is a real thing. Your body’s mostly water, and it can’t work right without it. So, remember to stay hydrated, and drink plenty!

Text.SourceString: Sorry, I often sound stuffy in the morning.//But it usually clears up later.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, I often sound stuffy in the morning.//But it usually clears up later.

Text.SourceString: It’s important to be aware of our allergies.//You really don’t want to discover an allergy accidentally.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s important to be aware of our allergies.//You really don’t want to discover an allergy accidentally.

Text.SourceString: Especially not when you’re in the middle of a hot date.//Take a bite of that clam, then a rash suddenly breaks out, and your lips start to swell.//<portrait=happy><Italic>Not</> based on personal experience… *winks*
Text.LocalizedString: Especially not when you’re in the middle of a hot date.//Take a bite of that clam, then a rash suddenly breaks out, and your lips start to swell.//<portrait=happy><Italic>Not</> based on personal experience… *winks*

Text.SourceString: Work hard. But more importantly, work smart.//Don’t overexert yourself and pass out, or you’ll be billed for a medical emergency.
Text.LocalizedString: Work hard. But more importantly, work smart.//Don’t overexert yourself and pass out, or you’ll be billed for a medical emergency.

Text.SourceString: We don’t charge an outrageous amount.//Just enough to cover the cost.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t charge an outrageous amount.//Just enough to cover the cost.

Text.SourceString: Health is wealth. Don’t forget that!//Your money means nothing if you’re not healthy enough to enjoy it.
Text.LocalizedString: Health is wealth. Don’t forget that!//Your money means nothing if you’re not healthy enough to enjoy it.

Text.SourceString: I should make a poster about that and hang it here.
Text.LocalizedString: I should make a poster about that and hang it here.

Text.SourceString: New fashion trends are cool, but on other people.//I’m pretty comfortable with my style, so I’m sticking with it.
Text.LocalizedString: New fashion trends are cool, but on other people.//I’m pretty comfortable with my style, so I’m sticking with it.

Text.SourceString: Too much change makes me nervous.
Text.LocalizedString: Too much change makes me nervous.

Text.SourceString: I wear my green button-down when I’m feeling daring.//<portrait=happy>Have you seen me in it?//<portrait=normal>It makes for quite the outfit, I’ve been told.
Text.LocalizedString: I wear my green button-down when I’m feeling daring.//<portrait=happy>Have you seen me in it?//<portrait=normal>It makes for quite the outfit, I’ve been told.

Text.SourceString: Uh-oh! I hope I don’t sound vain. That’s not what I mean.//<portrait=concerned>*mumbles* Oh no, I’m starting to sound like <NpcName>Scott</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Uh-oh! I hope I don’t sound vain. That’s not what I mean.//<portrait=concerned>*mumbles* Oh no, I’m starting to sound like <NpcName>Scott</>.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Charles</> is singing off key.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Charles</> is singing off key.]

Text.SourceString: People here are kind.//It was the right move to choose Starlet Town as my forever home.
Text.LocalizedString: People here are kind.//It was the right move to choose Starlet Town as my forever home.

Text.SourceString: I feel very safe here. This is home to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel very safe here. This is home to me.

Text.SourceString: The first time I met <NPCName>Leah</> was…scary.//<portrait=sad>She used to scare me.
Text.LocalizedString: The first time I met <NPCName>Leah</> was…scary.//<portrait=sad>She used to scare me.

Text.SourceString: Well, even now, actually. <NPCName>Leah</> can be a touch intimidating.//<portrait=concerned>A little, yeah…
Text.LocalizedString: Well, even now, actually. <NPCName>Leah</> can be a touch intimidating.//<portrait=concerned>A little, yeah…

Text.SourceString: I have this ritual that I’ve been doing for who knows how long.//On Saturdays, I like to make burritos and keep the leftovers for Sunday’s lunch.//<portrait=happy>Are you like that too?
Text.LocalizedString: I have this ritual that I’ve been doing for who knows how long.//On Saturdays, I like to make burritos and keep the leftovers for Sunday’s lunch.//<portrait=happy>Are you like that too?

Text.SourceString: It's okay to let loose on special occasions, I suppose.//But we should always remember not to get carried away... I-I mean, it's important to exercise caution and not go overboard, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: It's okay to let loose on special occasions, I suppose.//But we should always remember not to get carried away... I-I mean, it's important to exercise caution and not go overboard, you know?

Text.SourceString: Ha ha. What can I say? I should really follow my own medical advice sometimes.//<portrait=happy>Um, certain things are just easier said than done, especially when burritos are involved! Heh...
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha. What can I say? I should really follow my own medical advice sometimes.//<portrait=happy>Um, certain things are just easier said than done, especially when burritos are involved! Heh...

Text.SourceString: It's important to get your health checked regularly.//If something's wrong, it's better to catch it early... I mean, it's crucial for early detection and prevention.
Text.LocalizedString: It's important to get your health checked regularly.//If something's wrong, it's better to catch it early... I mean, it's crucial for early detection and prevention.

Text.SourceString: Your mental health is just as important as your physical health.//If either is suffering, it could be catastrophic.
Text.LocalizedString: Your mental health is just as important as your physical health.//If either is suffering, it could be catastrophic.

Text.SourceString: I'm sorry, I don't mean to scare you or anything. It's just...the truth.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm sorry, I don't mean to scare you or anything. It's just...the truth.

Text.SourceString: We need to start talking about mental health more, so we can erase the social stigma around it.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to start talking about mental health more, so we can erase the social stigma around it.

Text.SourceString: That way, we could detect mental illness faster and easier.//<portrait=happy>I mean, early intervention is...um, crucial for maintaining good health, you see?
Text.LocalizedString: That way, we could detect mental illness faster and easier.//<portrait=happy>I mean, early intervention is...um, crucial for maintaining good health, you see?

Text.SourceString: Um, a hobby can help you relax and improve your overall well-being in the long run.//So if you don’t already have a hobby, maybe you could consider...um, reading or maybe even...uh, picking up a fishing rod... If that's something you're interested in.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, a hobby can help you relax and improve your overall well-being in the long run.//So if you don’t already have a hobby, maybe you could consider...um, reading or maybe even...uh, picking up a fishing rod... If that's something you're interested in.

Text.SourceString: Um, excuse me, but is my hair...uh, messy? I hope not...
Text.LocalizedString: Um, excuse me, but is my hair...uh, messy? I hope not...

Text.SourceString: Oh, you said "lazy." I thought you said my hair was...<Italic>messy</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, um, please don't startle me like that! I'm not being lazy, I'm just taking a short break.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you said "lazy." I thought you said my hair was...<Italic>messy</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, um, please don't startle me like that! I'm not being lazy, I'm just taking a short break.

Text.SourceString: One day not long from now, my hair will be gone. So I'm trying to cherish every strand while I still can.//<portrait=surprised>N-not that there's anything wrong with going bald.//<portrait=annoyed>I'm just imagining how warm it would be under the sun...um, hypothetically speaking.
Text.LocalizedString: One day not long from now, my hair will be gone. So I'm trying to cherish every strand while I still can.//<portrait=surprised>N-not that there's anything wrong with going bald.//<portrait=annoyed>I'm just imagining how warm it would be under the sun...um, hypothetically speaking.

Text.SourceString: I might have to remember to apply sunscreen to my head if I become bald.//<portrait=concerned>Or, um, perhaps wearing a hat would be a good idea.
Text.LocalizedString: I might have to remember to apply sunscreen to my head if I become bald.//<portrait=concerned>Or, um, perhaps wearing a hat would be a good idea.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Scott's</> a bit...messy, yeah. And he tends to leave things all over the place.//<portrait=normal>But, um, aside from that, he's actually a...a decent housemate, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Scott's</> a bit...messy, yeah. And he tends to leave things all over the place.//<portrait=normal>But, um, aside from that, he's actually a...a decent housemate, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: That said, he...um, often walks straight into doors. Not just screen doors, but regular solid ones too.//<portrait=annoyed>It's quite surprising how successful he is, given his...um, clumsiness.
Text.LocalizedString: That said, he...um, often walks straight into doors. Not just screen doors, but regular solid ones too.//<portrait=annoyed>It's quite surprising how successful he is, given his...um, clumsiness.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad everybody here has equal access to health care.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad everybody here has equal access to health care.

Text.SourceString: Health care is a basic human need.//So I don’t think wealth should determine whether or not somebody gets it.
Text.LocalizedString: Health care is a basic human need.//So I don’t think wealth should determine whether or not somebody gets it.

Text.SourceString: We’re lucky we never have to worry about health care.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a luxury in some parts of the world. Unfair, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re lucky we never have to worry about health care.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a luxury in some parts of the world. Unfair, I know.

Text.SourceString: Our clinic only charges for emergency services.//And even then, we’re highly subsidized by the government, so everybody pays what they can afford.
Text.LocalizedString: Our clinic only charges for emergency services.//And even then, we’re highly subsidized by the government, so everybody pays what they can afford.

Text.SourceString: In all my years at the clinic, I've never turned anyone away in need.//That's...um, not what we stand for here.//We believe in providing care and support to everyone, because that's the right thing to do.
Text.LocalizedString: In all my years at the clinic, I've never turned anyone away in need.//That's...um, not what we stand for here.//We believe in providing care and support to everyone, because that's the right thing to do.

Text.SourceString: I could go for a burrito right now.//<portrait=normal>And maybe...some strawberries later.
Text.LocalizedString: I could go for a burrito right now.//<portrait=normal>And maybe...some strawberries later.

Text.SourceString: I try to match my tie to my hair. It’s hard to choose the right shade sometimes.//But thankfully, I managed to figure it out somehow.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to match my tie to my hair. It’s hard to choose the right shade sometimes.//But thankfully, I managed to figure it out somehow.

Text.SourceString: Being seen next to <NpcName>Yuri</> can be overwhelming for me.//She's so...vibrant and green, it's...um, quite striking, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: Being seen next to <NpcName>Yuri</> can be overwhelming for me.//She's so...vibrant and green, it's...um, quite striking, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: Milk gives me an upset stomach, so I try to avoid it.//Honestly, I...um, I'd rather not drink it at all.
Text.LocalizedString: Milk gives me an upset stomach, so I try to avoid it.//Honestly, I...um, I'd rather not drink it at all.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to reduce my dairy intake. But some things are harder to cut out than others.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to reduce my dairy intake. But some things are harder to cut out than others.

Text.SourceString: The last time I went out dancing? Hmm… Has to have been last week.
Text.LocalizedString: The last time I went out dancing? Hmm… Has to have been last week.

Text.SourceString: You seem interested in my dancing schedule. You’re not going to take me out dancing, are ya?//<portrait=normal>’Cause I wouldn’t say no. *chuckles*
Text.LocalizedString: You seem interested in my dancing schedule. You’re not going to take me out dancing, are ya?//<portrait=normal>’Cause I wouldn’t say no. *chuckles*

Text.SourceString: Today isn’t a good day to go to the Tavern. Trust me!//It’s so busy on weekends. Phew!
Text.LocalizedString: Today isn’t a good day to go to the Tavern. Trust me!//It’s so busy on weekends. Phew!

Text.SourceString: There are so many people, there’s no room to dance.//What’s the point of going if I’m not going to dance, right? I prefer to go on Fridays.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many people, there’s no room to dance.//What’s the point of going if I’m not going to dance, right? I prefer to go on Fridays.

Text.SourceString: I popped into the Tavern to see if anybody was there, but then I just left.//I wasn’t really feeling it today.
Text.LocalizedString: I popped into the Tavern to see if anybody was there, but then I just left.//I wasn’t really feeling it today.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Charles</> is mumbling incomprehensible gibberish.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Charles</> is mumbling incomprehensible gibberish.]

Text.SourceString: H-Hey, I'm not mumbling incomprehensible gibberish!//I’m trying to remember the medicines I need to restock.
Text.LocalizedString: H-Hey, I'm not mumbling incomprehensible gibberish!//I’m trying to remember the medicines I need to restock.

Text.SourceString: Uh-oh, here it comes. Spring allergies.
Text.LocalizedString: Uh-oh, here it comes. Spring allergies.

Text.SourceString: Hold on a–//<portrait=surprised>*achoo!*//<portrait=normal>What I was saying was–//<portrait=surprised>*achoo!*//<portrait=normal>Okay. I think I’m good now. Where were we?
Text.LocalizedString: Hold on a–//<portrait=surprised>*achoo!*//<portrait=normal>What I was saying was–//<portrait=surprised>*achoo!*//<portrait=normal>Okay. I think I’m good now. Where were we?

Text.SourceString: Life must be exciting right now for farmers like you.
Text.LocalizedString: Life must be exciting right now for farmers like you.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you know, with the new season and all.//<portrait=happy>It’s, um, an ideal time for farming, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you know, with the new season and all.//<portrait=happy>It’s, um, an ideal time for farming, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I’d apply more sunscreen in about an hour if I were you.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry, I always say.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I’d apply more sunscreen in about an hour if I were you.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry, I always say.

Text.SourceString: I’m keeping my windows closed for the whole season.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m keeping my windows closed for the whole season.

Text.SourceString: I know what you’re gonna say. I should probably take allergy medicine, right? But it makes me really drowsy.//Haven’t found the right one, probably.
Text.LocalizedString: I know what you’re gonna say. I should probably take allergy medicine, right? But it makes me really drowsy.//Haven’t found the right one, probably.

Text.SourceString: I always change clothes as soon as I get home.// You don’t want to sleep with pollen sticking to your clothes and hair and stuff. *shivers*
Text.LocalizedString: I always change clothes as soon as I get home.// You don’t want to sleep with pollen sticking to your clothes and hair and stuff. *shivers*

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad <NPCName>Yuri</> is here. She’s made of iron, that one.//I would’ve been miserable running the clinic alone with all this pollen flying around.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad <NPCName>Yuri</> is here. She’s made of iron, that one.//I would’ve been miserable running the clinic alone with all this pollen flying around.

Text.SourceString: I like the weather, but Spring’s gotta be at the bottom of my list of favorite seasons.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the weather, but Spring’s gotta be at the bottom of my list of favorite seasons.

Text.SourceString: My allergies are like clockwork, <PlayerName>$player</>. On the 1st of Spring, that’s it for me.
Text.LocalizedString: My allergies are like clockwork, <PlayerName>$player</>. On the 1st of Spring, that’s it for me.

Text.SourceString: I feel like myself again! No more endless sniffling!
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like myself again! No more endless sniffling!

Text.SourceString: Now that the pollen has calmed down, I can...um, I can open my windows again.//Nothing beats waking up in the fresh air.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that the pollen has calmed down, I can...um, I can open my windows again.//Nothing beats waking up in the fresh air.

Text.SourceString: I have to say, hot weather isn’t my thing.//It puffs up my hair like cotton candy.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say, hot weather isn’t my thing.//It puffs up my hair like cotton candy.

Text.SourceString: It's good that more people are out and about in Summer. J-Just...um, don't forget the sunscreen, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: It's good that more people are out and about in Summer. J-Just...um, don't forget the sunscreen, okay?

Text.SourceString: The humidity isn’t helping my hair at all.//Yours is fine, though. How come? What shampoo do you use?
Text.LocalizedString: The humidity isn’t helping my hair at all.//Yours is fine, though. How come? What shampoo do you use?

Text.SourceString: People may call me...um, annoying for it, but I'll keep reminding them about sunscreen.//Especially in this scorching Summer sun.
Text.LocalizedString: People may call me...um, annoying for it, but I'll keep reminding them about sunscreen.//Especially in this scorching Summer sun.

Text.SourceString: I've already had to treat a few people for sunburn...//<portrait=surprised>I won't name any names, <PlayerName>$player</>. Doctor-patient confidentiality and all that.
Text.LocalizedString: I've already had to treat a few people for sunburn...//<portrait=surprised>I won't name any names, <PlayerName>$player</>. Doctor-patient confidentiality and all that.

Text.SourceString: Daisies...um, they don't make me sneeze too much unless I get really close.//So, I just try to avoid places where they grow.
Text.LocalizedString: Daisies...um, they don't make me sneeze too much unless I get really close.//So, I just try to avoid places where they grow.

Text.SourceString: I just love Fall. There’s all the warming comfort food, and it’s not too hot or too cold outside.//It’s perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: I just love Fall. There’s all the warming comfort food, and it’s not too hot or too cold outside.//It’s perfect.

Text.SourceString: The best thing about Fall is definitely sweet potato chips.//Sure, I could get them in other seasons, but they’re just better in Fall, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: The best thing about Fall is definitely sweet potato chips.//Sure, I could get them in other seasons, but they’re just better in Fall, you know?

Text.SourceString: Nothing like the crisp Fall air for enjoying some sweet potato chips.//<portrait=annoyed>I wish I had some now…
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing like the crisp Fall air for enjoying some sweet potato chips.//<portrait=annoyed>I wish I had some now…

Text.SourceString: I’m better suited to colder weather, I think.//Not too many mosquitos, and I just wake up refreshed!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m better suited to colder weather, I think.//Not too many mosquitos, and I just wake up refreshed!

Text.SourceString: Have you, um, gotten your flu shot yet?//Winter is next week, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you, um, gotten your flu shot yet?//Winter is next week, you know.

Text.SourceString: Are you excited about the Harvest Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Well, I can't wait, but I'm a bit nervous too.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you excited about the Harvest Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Well, I can't wait, but I'm a bit nervous too.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Yuri</> and I are usually pretty busy this season.//The townsfolk always need us for something or other, whether it’s treating a cold or patching them up after a slip on the ice.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Yuri</> and I are usually pretty busy this season.//The townsfolk always need us for something or other, whether it’s treating a cold or patching them up after a slip on the ice.

Text.SourceString: Please take care of yourself this season, <PlayerName>$player</>. Winter can be tough on our health, with less sunlight and all...//And it's not just about the flu or colds. The Winter blues can really get to you.
Text.LocalizedString: Please take care of yourself this season, <PlayerName>$player</>. Winter can be tough on our health, with less sunlight and all...//And it's not just about the flu or colds. The Winter blues can really get to you.

Text.SourceString: Whew, another Winter's almost over...//Thankfully, there weren't many flu cases this year. I'm relieved.
Text.LocalizedString: Whew, another Winter's almost over...//Thankfully, there weren't many flu cases this year. I'm relieved.

Text.SourceString: I open my windows first thing in the morning.//I like to let the cold air in.
Text.LocalizedString: I open my windows first thing in the morning.//I like to let the cold air in.

Text.SourceString: You need to layer up when you leave the house, especially in Winter.//Another tip: wash your hands when you get home. Some viruses thrive in cold, dry conditions.
Text.LocalizedString: You need to layer up when you leave the house, especially in Winter.//Another tip: wash your hands when you get home. Some viruses thrive in cold, dry conditions.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Festival. Are you? I can’t wait for the present exchange and eating all the good food.//<NPCName>Bree</> is an amazing host!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Festival. Are you? I can’t wait for the present exchange and eating all the good food.//<NPCName>Bree</> is an amazing host!

Text.SourceString: Ah, finally, a cool breeze!
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, finally, a cool breeze!

Text.SourceString: Wow, seems like my hair matches the season…
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, seems like my hair matches the season…

Text.SourceString: It’s bright yet soothing, vibrant yet refreshing, crisp yet soft, and full of warmth.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s bright yet soothing, vibrant yet refreshing, crisp yet soft, and full of warmth.

Text.SourceString: I guess farmers like your good self must be busy this season, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I guess farmers like your good self must be busy this season, eh?

Text.SourceString: What do you mean, why? It’s Fall. Some even call it the harvest season.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you mean, why? It’s Fall. Some even call it the harvest season.

Text.SourceString: I'm feeling a bit, um, low.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm feeling a bit, um, low.

Text.SourceString: I blame the snow. Well, at least the dinner party is coming up soon, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I blame the snow. Well, at least the dinner party is coming up soon, eh?

Text.SourceString: All this snow must be challenging for people in your trade.//Farming and the snowy season… Tough business.
Text.LocalizedString: All this snow must be challenging for people in your trade.//Farming and the snowy season… Tough business.

Text.SourceString: I’m noticing that compared to other seasons, there’s less variety of fresh produce at <NpcName>Sam’s</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m noticing that compared to other seasons, there’s less variety of fresh produce at <NpcName>Sam’s</>.

Text.SourceString: Time passes so quickly these days. Just like falling raindrops.//There one second, gone the next.
Text.LocalizedString: Time passes so quickly these days. Just like falling raindrops.//There one second, gone the next.

Text.SourceString: I don't think I'll venture out today.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't think I'll venture out today.

Text.SourceString: Rainy days like this are a rare opportunity to catch up on some paperwork.
Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days like this are a rare opportunity to catch up on some paperwork.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll stop by the Tavern after work to warm up.//On rainy days like this, I bet it’s busier than ever.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll stop by the Tavern after work to warm up.//On rainy days like this, I bet it’s busier than ever.

Text.SourceString: People just don’t like to walk around in the rain, and I guess they get bored sitting around at home.
Text.LocalizedString: People just don’t like to walk around in the rain, and I guess they get bored sitting around at home.

Text.SourceString: Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work.
Text.LocalizedString: Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work.

Text.SourceString: Is my hair okay? I think the rain messed it up on the way here.
Text.LocalizedString: Is my hair okay? I think the rain messed it up on the way here.

Text.SourceString: Is <NpcName>Millie</> looking this way? How do I look?
Text.LocalizedString: Is <NpcName>Millie</> looking this way? How do I look?

Text.SourceString: Fancy seeing you here this late, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Fancy seeing you here this late, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: What? Why are you looking at me like that?
Text.LocalizedString: What? Why are you looking at me like that?

Text.SourceString: Do I have something in my hair?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I have something in my hair?

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll go out today.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll go out today.

Text.SourceString: It’s a good time to catch up on some paperwork.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a good time to catch up on some paperwork.

Text.SourceString: I have to go…
Text.LocalizedString: I have to go…

Text.SourceString: It’s late.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s late.

Text.SourceString: I’ll be out late today. I don’t want to be home all by myself.//I’m feeling kinda lonely.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll be out late today. I don’t want to be home all by myself.//I’m feeling kinda lonely.

Text.SourceString: Time flies on snowy days.
Text.LocalizedString: Time flies on snowy days.

Text.SourceString: Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work. Get your body moving and warm up.
Text.LocalizedString: Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work. Get your body moving and warm up.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something. The loneliness hits differently when you’re home alone on a snowy day.//It makes you not want to be at home.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something. The loneliness hits differently when you’re home alone on a snowy day.//It makes you not want to be at home.

Text.SourceString: Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>, need some more vitamins?
Text.LocalizedString: Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>, need some more vitamins?

Text.SourceString: Don’t shame a man for trying to sell his products, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>Vitamins help you, and they help me at the same time. I don’t know what you’re talking about.//It doesn’t sound shady to me at all.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t shame a man for trying to sell his products, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>Vitamins help you, and they help me at the same time. I don’t know what you’re talking about.//It doesn’t sound shady to me at all.

Text.SourceString: Are you okay? You look a bit flushed and sweaty.//<portrait=normal>I think you might need some medicine.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you okay? You look a bit flushed and sweaty.//<portrait=normal>I think you might need some medicine.

Text.SourceString: What brings you here, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>Are you alright?
Text.LocalizedString: What brings you here, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>Are you alright?

Text.SourceString: Watch your step! Slippery floor!
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step! Slippery floor!

Text.SourceString: We disinfect the clinic according to international standards, especially after an emergency visit.//Excellent hygiene is critical in health care.
Text.LocalizedString: We disinfect the clinic according to international standards, especially after an emergency visit.//Excellent hygiene is critical in health care.

Text.SourceString: It can get a bit too bright in here sometimes. Makes it hard for me to nap.
Text.LocalizedString: It can get a bit too bright in here sometimes. Makes it hard for me to nap.

Text.SourceString: Just kidding, of course. *nervous chuckle*
Text.LocalizedString: Just kidding, of course. *nervous chuckle*

Text.SourceString: Remember to use your sunscreen.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to use your sunscreen.

Text.SourceString: This morning, I woke up and I just, um, realized that this island is filled with clean air and nice people.
Text.LocalizedString: This morning, I woke up and I just, um, realized that this island is filled with clean air and nice people.

Text.SourceString: It feels like it's going to be a good day... I think!
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like it's going to be a good day... I think!

Text.SourceString: If you get a cut or a scrape, wash it right away with running water.//It'll help clean the wound.
Text.LocalizedString: If you get a cut or a scrape, wash it right away with running water.//It'll help clean the wound.

Text.SourceString: *sneezes* You never know when allergies will hit.
Text.LocalizedString: *sneezes* You never know when allergies will hit.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe people want to drill for oil here, of all places.//<portrait=normal>This island is beautiful!//Before the oil spill happened, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe people want to drill for oil here, of all places.//<portrait=normal>This island is beautiful!//Before the oil spill happened, anyway.

Text.SourceString: I hope you're not overfeeding your pet.//Playing with them when they're bored is...well, better than just giving them treats, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you're not overfeeding your pet.//Playing with them when they're bored is...well, better than just giving them treats, I think.

Text.SourceString: Right, I, um, I don't have any pets...//<portrait=normal>But that doesn't mean I don't know a thing or two about them.
Text.LocalizedString: Right, I, um, I don't have any pets...//<portrait=normal>But that doesn't mean I don't know a thing or two about them.

Text.SourceString: *sneezes* Oh, sorry. The flowers. This season…really gets to me… *sneezes*
Text.LocalizedString: *sneezes* Oh, sorry. The flowers. This season…really gets to me… *sneezes*

Text.SourceString: I’m okay… Thanks!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m okay… Thanks!

Text.SourceString: Do you, um, come here often?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you, um, come here often?

Text.SourceString: Glad to see you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Glad to see you, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Two drinks and I’m done. Anything more and it’s hangover city for me the next day.
Text.LocalizedString: Two drinks and I’m done. Anything more and it’s hangover city for me the next day.

Text.SourceString: Ah, who am I kidding? My hair isn’t this bright.//I’ve got gray hair, <PlayerName>$player</>! That’s why I keep revamping the color.//<portrait=concerned>Oh jeez. Do youngsters still say “revamping”?
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, who am I kidding? My hair isn’t this bright.//I’ve got gray hair, <PlayerName>$player</>! That’s why I keep revamping the color.//<portrait=concerned>Oh jeez. Do youngsters still say “revamping”?

Text.SourceString: They don’t say “youngsters” anymore, do they?//<portrait=concerned>My age is showing.
Text.LocalizedString: They don’t say “youngsters” anymore, do they?//<portrait=concerned>My age is showing.

Text.SourceString: Never once in my life have I come here intending to buy anything, but somehow, I always buy something I don’t need.
Text.LocalizedString: Never once in my life have I come here intending to buy anything, but somehow, I always buy something I don’t need.

Text.SourceString: If my pollen allergy weren’t so bad, I’d buy some flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: If my pollen allergy weren’t so bad, I’d buy some flowers.

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of wild fruits around here.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of wild fruits around here.

Text.SourceString: Oh, um, what am I reading? Just some medical journals and fashion magazines.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, um, what am I reading? Just some medical journals and fashion magazines.

Text.SourceString: I'm just having a chat with <NpcName>Suki</>.//It's a bit too hot for me to be outside.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm just having a chat with <NpcName>Suki</>.//It's a bit too hot for me to be outside.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe how bright it is outside today.//If it weren’t for that ice-cold wind, you’d think it was Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe how bright it is outside today.//If it weren’t for that ice-cold wind, you’d think it was Summer!

Text.SourceString: Ugh, I don’t think I put on enough sunscreen today. I hope they have extra!
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, I don’t think I put on enough sunscreen today. I hope they have extra!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sunny</> always tries to talk me into going fishing. Heh heh. Funny guy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sunny</> always tries to talk me into going fishing. Heh heh. Funny guy.

Text.SourceString: Nice to see you, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Nice to see you, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I found wild berries by the lighthouse the other day!
Text.LocalizedString: I found wild berries by the lighthouse the other day!

Text.SourceString: I’ve yet to see this place packed.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve yet to see this place packed.

Text.SourceString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to make sure <NpcName>Millie</> is doing well.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to make sure <NpcName>Millie</> is doing well.

Text.SourceString: Errr… I mean, to make sure her tasks are done on time.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr… I mean, to make sure her tasks are done on time.

Text.SourceString: I’m checking out a couple of books today to read over the next week.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m checking out a couple of books today to read over the next week.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll head home after this...//I'm feeling pretty tired.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll head home after this...//I'm feeling pretty tired.

Text.SourceString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.

Text.SourceString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Because I’m off duty right now.

Text.SourceString: I tripped on a shoe and spilled my coffee this morning. What a Monday, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I tripped on a shoe and spilled my coffee this morning. What a Monday, eh?

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Charles</> looks confused, as if he forgot his lunch again.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Charles</> looks confused, as if he forgot his lunch again.]

Text.SourceString: I can hear you, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: I can hear you, you know.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I feel like I’m 150 years old. *chuckles* I went through way too much, too fast.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I feel like I’m 150 years old. *chuckles* I went through way too much, too fast.

Text.SourceString: Now I’m just looking for some peace and solitude.
Text.LocalizedString: Now I’m just looking for some peace and solitude.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t think my life would turn out like this.//<portrait=sad>I thought I’d be married and have a family of my own by now, but sometimes life throws you a curveball.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t think my life would turn out like this.//<portrait=sad>I thought I’d be married and have a family of my own by now, but sometimes life throws you a curveball.

Text.SourceString: Instead, I’m all alone, living in a house with an overgrown frat boy.//<portrait=happy>And that’s A-OK!
Text.LocalizedString: Instead, I’m all alone, living in a house with an overgrown frat boy.//<portrait=happy>And that’s A-OK!

Text.SourceString: I hate to admit this, but…//<portrait=normal>I like having <NpcName>Scott</> around because he makes the house feels less empty.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to admit this, but…//<portrait=normal>I like having <NpcName>Scott</> around because he makes the house feels less empty.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell <NpcName>Scott</>! I don’t want his head to get bigger than it already is. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell <NpcName>Scott</>! I don’t want his head to get bigger than it already is. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I came to Starlet Town right after I was licensed. I was being good. I was trying to have a normal life, make enough money to feed my family.//<portrait=annoyed>At the time, I was ready to settle down with my–
Text.LocalizedString: I came to Starlet Town right after I was licensed. I was being good. I was trying to have a normal life, make enough money to feed my family.//<portrait=annoyed>At the time, I was ready to settle down with my–

Text.SourceString: Let’s just say things don’t always go as planned.//<portrait=annoyed>But I learned you don’t have to worry about feeding your family if you don’t <Italic>have</> any family to feed.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s just say things don’t always go as planned.//<portrait=annoyed>But I learned you don’t have to worry about feeding your family if you don’t <Italic>have</> any family to feed.

Text.SourceString: Where did I put that book? Hmm. I have at least three books I need to return.
Text.LocalizedString: Where did I put that book? Hmm. I have at least three books I need to return.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Millie</> would be upset if I misplaced another one of her books.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d think that I’d have a better memory, being a doctor and all, wouldn’t you? But nope.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Millie</> would be upset if I misplaced another one of her books.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d think that I’d have a better memory, being a doctor and all, wouldn’t you? But nope.

Text.SourceString: Will you be going to the library after this, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I may have some stuff that you can return to <NpcName>Millie</> for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Will you be going to the library after this, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I may have some stuff that you can return to <NpcName>Millie</> for me.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re going to <NpcName>Sam’s</>, huh? Hmm. Let’s see. What do I need from <NpcName>Sam’s</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you’re going to <NpcName>Sam’s</>, huh? Hmm. Let’s see. What do I need from <NpcName>Sam’s</>?

Text.SourceString: My hair looks great today. It <Italic>feels</> great.//<portrait=happy>I think I have a great day ahead of me.
Text.LocalizedString: My hair looks great today. It <Italic>feels</> great.//<portrait=happy>I think I have a great day ahead of me.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Don’t touch it.//<portrait=sad>Sorry! I don’t want you to mess it up.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Don’t touch it.//<portrait=sad>Sorry! I don’t want you to mess it up.

Text.SourceString: I feel like I’m too uptight sometimes, so having a friend who’s alive, like <NpcName>Scott</>, can be good for my sanity.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like I’m too uptight sometimes, so having a friend who’s alive, like <NpcName>Scott</>, can be good for my sanity.

Text.SourceString: Did I just say “alive”? Oh gosh. Heh heh. I meant lively!//Someone <Italic>lively</> like <NpcName>Scott</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Did I just say “alive”? Oh gosh. Heh heh. I meant lively!//Someone <Italic>lively</> like <NpcName>Scott</>.

Text.SourceString: I can make home visits if necessary, yeah.//Just let me know when, and I’ll be there.
Text.LocalizedString: I can make home visits if necessary, yeah.//Just let me know when, and I’ll be there.

Text.SourceString: There aren’t many requests for home visits around here. Unless they’re badly injured or can’t get out of bed, people usually prefer to come to the clinic.//<portrait=normal>Oh, except for <NpcName>Walter</> and his family.
Text.LocalizedString: There aren’t many requests for home visits around here. Unless they’re badly injured or can’t get out of bed, people usually prefer to come to the clinic.//<portrait=normal>Oh, except for <NpcName>Walter</> and his family.

Text.SourceString: Oh goodness! You surprised me there, <Italic>buddy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh goodness! You surprised me there, <Italic>buddy</>.

Text.SourceString: Sorry I called you buddy. That felt kinda weird.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry I called you buddy. That felt kinda weird.

Text.SourceString: While you’re here, you should buy some vitamins to boost your health.
Text.LocalizedString: While you’re here, you should buy some vitamins to boost your health.

Text.SourceString: It’s good to have extra medicine on hand if you go down to the cavern.//Just in case.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to have extra medicine on hand if you go down to the cavern.//Just in case.

Text.SourceString: Looking for <NpcName>Yuri</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Looking for <NpcName>Yuri</>?

Text.SourceString: Oh my, it’s dead in here.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my, it’s dead in here.

Text.SourceString: A good thing, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: A good thing, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: You look good today, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: You look good today, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: What’s your diet like, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your diet like, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Diet is much more important than you realize.
Text.LocalizedString: Diet is much more important than you realize.

Text.SourceString: One of the things I wish all patients knew is that they should always be honest with their doctors.//We’re just trying to give the best care possible.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the things I wish all patients knew is that they should always be honest with their doctors.//We’re just trying to give the best care possible.

Text.SourceString: Psst… I tried to curl my hair back in the day.//<portrait=happy>Still have a picture of it somewhere at the house. Ha ha. I wish I didn’t.
Text.LocalizedString: Psst… I tried to curl my hair back in the day.//<portrait=happy>Still have a picture of it somewhere at the house. Ha ha. I wish I didn’t.

Text.SourceString: Oh boy… I don’t know why I told you that.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh boy… I don’t know why I told you that.

Text.SourceString: Should I order another cake?//I mean, I've been watching what I eat lately, so I feel like I deserve a little reward.
Text.LocalizedString: Should I order another cake?//I mean, I've been watching what I eat lately, so I feel like I deserve a little reward.

Text.SourceString: Have I told you about my ex?//Oh, here come the tears!
Text.LocalizedString: Have I told you about my ex?//Oh, here come the tears!

Text.SourceString: I should go home. I think I’ve had enough to drink.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go home. I think I’ve had enough to drink.

Text.SourceString: Not going to lie. I do envy <NpcName>Yuri</> sometimes.//She’s done so much with her life. What have I done? *sobs*
Text.LocalizedString: Not going to lie. I do envy <NpcName>Yuri</> sometimes.//She’s done so much with her life. What have I done? *sobs*

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t matter… I’m enough. I’m loved.//A little mantra my therapist taught me. *hic*
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t matter… I’m enough. I’m loved.//A little mantra my therapist taught me. *hic*

Text.SourceString: Cookies sound great right now.//The ones from <NpcName>Sam’s</> are my <Italic>kryptonite</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Cookies sound great right now.//The ones from <NpcName>Sam’s</> are my <Italic>kryptonite</>.

Text.SourceString: I like this color on me. Green, yeah!//<portrait=happy>It lifts my spirits.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this color on me. Green, yeah!//<portrait=happy>It lifts my spirits.

Text.SourceString: You always look fashionable, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//You must spend millions on clothes!
Text.LocalizedString: You always look fashionable, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//You must spend millions on clothes!

Text.SourceString: They look great on you.
Text.LocalizedString: They look great on you.

Text.SourceString: Wow! You look amazing in that.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! You look amazing in that.

Text.SourceString: We should hang out soon, at my place.//<portrait=normal>I’ll make pasta, pop open some wine.
Text.LocalizedString: We should hang out soon, at my place.//<portrait=normal>I’ll make pasta, pop open some wine.

Text.SourceString: Wow! You look incredibly hot in that.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! You look incredibly hot in that.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Charles</> looks flustered.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Charles</> looks flustered.]

Text.SourceString: I’m not looking for love. I told <NpcName>Scott</> love isn’t something we “look for.”//If it’s meant to be, it’ll come.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not looking for love. I told <NpcName>Scott</> love isn’t something we “look for.”//If it’s meant to be, it’ll come.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Scott</> worries that I’ll be alone if I’m still single when he moves out.//<portrait=normal>I don’t think he gets it. I don’t mind.//I like my own company.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Scott</> worries that I’ll be alone if I’m still single when he moves out.//<portrait=normal>I don’t think he gets it. I don’t mind.//I like my own company.

Text.SourceString: The mayor sets a great example for what people should wear in Summer.//Nice breezy clothing, a well-fitting hat.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor sets a great example for what people should wear in Summer.//Nice breezy clothing, a well-fitting hat.

Text.SourceString: This white coat is handy in Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>Wearing just scrubs is too cold for me. Way too cold.
Text.LocalizedString: This white coat is handy in Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>Wearing just scrubs is too cold for me. Way too cold.

Text.SourceString: I was talking to the mayor the other day, and he seemed down.//<portrait=normal>I’m going to check up on him tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I was talking to the mayor the other day, and he seemed down.//<portrait=normal>I’m going to check up on him tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: If he gets the Winter blues, vitamin D should help.//I’ll see if I can take him some.
Text.LocalizedString: If he gets the Winter blues, vitamin D should help.//I’ll see if I can take him some.

Text.SourceString: I told <NpcName>Sunny</> to keep up with his swimming. He’s great at it, too! One of the fastest swimmers in town.//<portrait=happy>Swimming is easy on the knees, and it keeps him healthy.
Text.LocalizedString: I told <NpcName>Sunny</> to keep up with his swimming. He’s great at it, too! One of the fastest swimmers in town.//<portrait=happy>Swimming is easy on the knees, and it keeps him healthy.

Text.SourceString: His son, <NpcName>Oliver</>, is a major incentive for him to stay healthy.
Text.LocalizedString: His son, <NpcName>Oliver</>, is a major incentive for him to stay healthy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sunny</> could use hearing aids, but he refuses.//<portrait=happy>I’m not too worried about it. It isn’t anything major.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sunny</> could use hearing aids, but he refuses.//<portrait=happy>I’m not too worried about it. It isn’t anything major.

Text.SourceString: You could technically eat flowers, but I can’t recommend it.//That’s just my personal opinion.
Text.LocalizedString: You could technically eat flowers, but I can’t recommend it.//That’s just my personal opinion.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing wrong with it, but why would you <Italic>want</> to eat flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing wrong with it, but why would you <Italic>want</> to eat flowers?

Text.SourceString: By the way, thanks for always being there for me.//I appreciate it.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, thanks for always being there for me.//I appreciate it.

Text.SourceString: I appreciate everything <NpcName>Scott’s</> done for me.//He’s a good friend.
Text.LocalizedString: I appreciate everything <NpcName>Scott’s</> done for me.//He’s a good friend.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and sunny today. I wish I could enjoy it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and sunny today. I wish I could enjoy it.

Text.SourceString: I like sunny days like these.
Text.LocalizedString: I like sunny days like these.

Text.SourceString: I bet we can see the stars tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I bet we can see the stars tonight.

Text.SourceString: Oof! My belt feels tight.//<portrait=angry>It must be all the cookies I ate last week.
Text.LocalizedString: Oof! My belt feels tight.//<portrait=angry>It must be all the cookies I ate last week.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to wash your hands often.//Flu season’s here.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to wash your hands often.//Flu season’s here.

Text.SourceString: Get your flu shot if you haven’t already.
Text.LocalizedString: Get your flu shot if you haven’t already.
